---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "VOO Dividend Analysis & History",
    "description": "Examine VOO's historical dividend data, long-term yield consistency, and reinvestment potential.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Westmount Fundamentals"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the voo dividend?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The voo dividend represents the collective dividend income generated by the 500 large-cap US companies within the Vanguard S&P 500 ETF, passed through to shareholders."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the current voo dividend yield?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Currently, the trailing 12-month voo dividend yield is approximately 1.12%. It fluctuates primarily based on the price appreciation of the underlying S&P 500 index."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Where can I find the voo dividend history?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The voo dividend history demonstrates steady, long-term growth as the underlying companies increase their payouts. We maintain a detailed 5-year table of every quarterly payment."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When is the next voo dividend date?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "VOO pays out dividends quarterly. The standard voo dividend date pattern falls in late March, June, September, and December."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I use a voo dividend calculator?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Our voo dividend calculator allows you to input your share count and average cost basis to estimate your annual and quarterly income based on the fund's trailing yield."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What was the voo dividend yield 2024?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The voo dividend yield 2024 remained near historical S&P 500 lows, largely due to massive price appreciation in mega-cap technology stocks pushing the index value higher."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the forecast for the voo dividend yield 2026?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "While nominal payouts are expected to rise, the voo dividend yield 2026 will heavily depend on index valuation. A market correction could raise the yield, while a bull run will likely keep it near 1-1.5%."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---

<SiteLayout
  site="westmount"
  title="VOO Dividend Analysis & History"
  description="How much passive income does the S&P 500 actually generate? Explore the precise payout metrics and history."
  canonical="https://westmountfundamentals.com/voo-dividend"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>VOO Dividend Analysis & History</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Long-term payout trends, S&P 500 yield metrics, and dividend calculator</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>VOO Dividend Profile</h2>
      <p>The Vanguard S&P 500 ETF (VOO) is the ultimate core holding for millions of investors. While primarily known for capital appreciation, it also provides a growing, reliable stream of dividend income from the 500 largest U.S. companies.</p>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Current Yield & Metrics</h3>
        <table>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th>Current Trailing Yield</th>
              <td>1.12%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Payout Frequency</th>
              <td>Quarterly</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Price-to-Earnings (P/E)</th>
              <td>26.70</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Expense Ratio</th>
              <td>0.03%</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p>Unlike high-yield funds, VOO's primary goal is total return. The yield often appears low primarily because the share price has appreciated so rapidly. If you are looking for pure income strategies, you may prefer options detailed in our <a href="/high-dividend-stocks">High Dividend Stocks Guide</a> or consider our <a href="/jepi-dividend">JEPI Dividend Analysis</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5-Year Dividend History</h2>
      <p>A hallmark of VOO is its consistent, long-term dividend growth. The table below details the quarterly payouts over the last 5 years.</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Ex-Dividend Date</th>
            <th>Amount ($)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>2025-12-22</td><td>$1.7710</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-09-29</td><td>$1.7400</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-06-30</td><td>$1.7450</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2025-03-27</td><td>$1.8120</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-12-23</td><td>$1.7390</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-09-27</td><td>$1.6390</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-06-28</td><td>$1.7840</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2024-03-22</td><td>$1.5430</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2023-12-20</td><td>$1.8010</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2023-09-28</td><td>$1.4930</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2023-06-29</td><td>$1.5760</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2023-03-24</td><td>$1.4870</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2022-12-20</td><td>$1.6720</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2022-09-28</td><td>$1.4690</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2022-06-29</td><td>$1.4320</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2022-03-24</td><td>$1.3740</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2021-12-21</td><td>$1.5330</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2021-09-29</td><td>$1.3080</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2021-06-29</td><td>$1.3330</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2021-03-26</td><td>$1.2630</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Dividend Reinvestment Calculator</h2>
      <p>Estimate the passive income generated by your core index position. Reinvesting these dividends over decades is the key to compound interest.</p>

      <div class="card" id="calc-container">
        <label style="display:block; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">Number of Shares Owned</label>
        <input type="number" id="sharesInput" placeholder="e.g. 50" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:8px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary); font-size:1rem; margin-bottom:1rem;" />

        <label style="display:block; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">Average Price per Share ($)</label>
        <input type="number" id="priceInput" placeholder="e.g. 450.00" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:8px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary); font-size:1rem; margin-bottom:1.5rem;" />

        <button id="calculateBtn" style="background:var(--accent-color); color:#fff; padding:0.75rem 1.5rem; border:none; border-radius:8px; font-weight:600; cursor:pointer; width:100%; font-size:1rem;">Calculate Income</button>

        <div id="results" style="display:none; margin-top:1.5rem; padding-top:1.5rem; border-top:1px solid var(--border-color);">
          <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
            <span style="color:var(--text-secondary);">Estimated Annual Income:</span>
            <span id="annualIncome" style="font-weight:700; color:var(--accent-color);">$0.00</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between;">
            <span style="color:var(--text-secondary);">Estimated Quarterly Payout:</span>
            <span id="quarterlyIncome" style="font-weight:700;">$0.00</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the voo dividend?</summary>
        <p>The voo dividend represents the collective dividend income generated by the 500 large-cap US companies within the Vanguard S&P 500 ETF, passed through to shareholders.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the current voo dividend yield?</summary>
        <p>Currently, the trailing 12-month voo dividend yield is approximately 1.12%. It fluctuates primarily based on the price appreciation of the underlying S&P 500 index.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Where can I find the voo dividend history?</summary>
        <p>The voo dividend history demonstrates steady, long-term growth as the underlying companies increase their payouts. We maintain a detailed 5-year table of every quarterly payment.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>When is the next voo dividend date?</summary>
        <p>VOO pays out dividends quarterly. The standard voo dividend date pattern falls in late March, June, September, and December.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do I use a voo dividend calculator?</summary>
        <p>Our voo dividend calculator allows you to input your share count and average cost basis to estimate your annual and quarterly income based on the fund's trailing yield.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What was the voo dividend yield 2024?</summary>
        <p>The voo dividend yield 2024 remained near historical S&P 500 lows, largely due to massive price appreciation in mega-cap technology stocks pushing the index value higher.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the forecast for the voo dividend yield 2026?</summary>
        <p>While nominal payouts are expected to rise, the voo dividend yield 2026 will heavily depend on index valuation. A market correction could raise the yield, while a bull run will likely keep it near 1-1.5%.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const btn = document.getElementById('calculateBtn');
      const sharesInput = document.getElementById('sharesInput');
      const priceInput = document.getElementById('priceInput');
      const resultsDiv = document.getElementById('results');
      const annualSpan = document.getElementById('annualIncome');
      const quarterlySpan = document.getElementById('quarterlyIncome');

      const YIELD = 0.0112; // 1.12%

      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const shares = parseFloat(sharesInput.value) || 0;
        const price = parseFloat(priceInput.value) || 0;

        const totalValue = shares * price;
        const annual = totalValue * YIELD;
        const quarterly = annual / 4;

        annualSpan.textContent = '$' + annual.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2});
        quarterlySpan.textContent = '$' + quarterly.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2});

        resultsDiv.style.display = 'block';
      });
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    th, td { padding: 0.75rem 1rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    th { font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
    a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
